Core Two Pointer Patterns in Arrays :

Here are the main categories you must master.
Each category has classic problems that interviewers love:

Pair Sum Problems :
    Two Sum in sorted array
    Count pairs with given sum
    Check if pair exists with difference K

Duplicate Handling
    Remove duplicates from sorted array
    Move zeros to end
    Remove element in-place

Reversal & Rearrangement
    Reverse array/string in-place
    Sort colors (Dutch National Flag)
    Partition array around pivot

Triplet & Subset Problems
    3-Sum (sum to zero)
    3-Sum closest to target
    Count triplets with sum less than target

Window & Subarray Problems
    Longest substring with K distinct characters
    Minimum window substring
    Subarray product less than K

Comparison Between Arrays
    Merge two sorted arrays
    Intersection of two arrays
    Find common elements in three sorted arrays

Max/Min Optimization
    Container With Most Water
    Trapping Rain Water (variation with two pointers)
    Maximize sum of min pairs

🎯 Most Asked MNC-Level Questions

    Two Sum in sorted array
    Remove duplicates from sorted array
    3-Sum problem
    Container With Most Water
    Dutch National Flag problem
    Merge two sorted arrays
    Minimum window substring

🧩 Quick Recognition Checklist
When you see a question, ask:

Do I need to scan from both ends? → Two pointers.

Do I need to maintain a window (start & end)? → Two pointers + sliding window.

Do I need to compare/merge sorted arrays? → Two pointers.

If yes → it’s almost certainly a two pointer problem